Title: Rule "Check Email": Option "Disable certificate validation"
Class: fix
Compatible: compat
Component: checks
Date: 1674551935
Edition: cre
Knowledge: doc
Level: 1
Version: 2.1.0p20

If the option "Disable certificate validation" -> "Ignore unsuccessful validation (in case of TLS/SSL)" under "Mail Receving"/"Connection settings" in the "Check Email" rule configuration is enabled, the corresponding service will return an error
C+:
check_mail: error: unrecognized arguments: --fetch-disable-cert-validation
C-:

This has now been fixed.
